@startuml IA_Alert_Sequence
autonumber
skinparam handwritten true

participant Frontend
participant Backend
participant "AI Service" as IA
database DB
participant "Storage (uploads/exams)" as Storage
participant WebSocket
participant "Mail Service" as Mail
participant "Center Admin" as Admin
participant Doctor
participant "Super Admin" as SuperAdmin

note over SuperAdmin
  Rôle de gouvernance clinique:
  - Définir les centres, les comptes administrateurs et les règles globales
  - Superviser les seuils d'alerte, l'audit et la qualité du dispositif
end note

note over Admin
  Rôle clinique opérationnel:
  - Enregistrer le patient et l'examen
  - Déclencher l'analyse IA et joindre les images
  - Assurer le suivi administratif du dossier
end note

note over Doctor
  Rôle clinique de validation:
  - Recevoir les alertes critiques
  - Vérifier l'interprétation IA et l'historique du patient
  - Confirmer la conduite à tenir et le suivi
end note

== Analyse IA & alerting ==

Frontend -> Backend : POST /exams (image_path)
activate Backend

Backend -> Storage : Ensure file exists
Storage --> Backend : image_path

Backend -> Backend : If DICOM and no preview -> convert
note right: call convert_dicom_to_jpeg.py
Backend -> Storage : save preview.jpg
Storage --> Backend : preview_path

Backend -> IA : POST /analyse (image_path or preview_path)  /* async */
activate IA
IA -> IA : Prétraitement, prédiction, confiance, heatmap
IA --> Backend : {grade, confidence, heatmap_bytes}
deactivate IA

Backend -> Storage : Save heatmap
Storage --> Backend : heatmap_path

Backend -> DB : INSERT exam (image_path, preview_path, heatmap_path, grade, confidence)
DB --> Backend : exam_id

Backend -> WebSocket : Push exam result (exam_id, grade, confidence, heatmap_path)
WebSocket --> Frontend : Push result

alt grade >= CRITICAL_THRESHOLD
    Backend -> DB : INSERT alert (exam_id, patient_id, doctor_id, priority='critical')
    DB --> Backend : alert_id
    Backend -> Mail : Send alert email (async)
    Mail --> Doctor : Email
    Backend -> WebSocket : Push alert (alert_id)
    WebSocket --> Frontend : Push alert
end

== Error handling ==

IA --> Backend : (timeout / error)
Backend -> Backend : Log error, mark exam status='analysis_failed'
Backend -> DB : Update exam status
DB --> Backend : ok
Backend -> WebSocket : Push error notification
WebSocket --> Frontend : Push error

note left of Backend
  Recommendations:
  - Make conversion & IA calls asynchronous with timeouts
  - Backfill job for failed conversions
  - Store only paths in DB, keep files on server disk
end note

deactivate Backend
@enduml